value.title: U.S. admits first group of asylum-seekers as Biden rolls back Remain-in-Mexico policy
value.excerpt: As part of its efforts to wind down a Trump-era policy that kept tens of thousands of asylum-seekers outside U.S. territory, the Biden administration on Friday admitted the first group of migrants who had been previously required to wait in Mexico for their immigration court hearings.

value.title: Trump ally Nunes sees CNN Ukraine lawsuit thrown out by New York judge

value.title: Cruz and Cuomo Face Scandal. Trump Can’t Save Them.
value.excerpt: Without Donald Trump dominating the political conversation, politicians’ audacious behavior isn’t so quickly subsumed.

value.title: Democrats Beat Trump in 2020. Now They’re Asking: What Went Wrong?
value.excerpt: Disappointed by down-ballot losses, Democratic interest groups are joining forces to conduct an autopsy of the election results. Republicans do not yet seem willing to reckon with the G.O.P.’s major defeats.

value.title: Trump freeze-out: De Blasio puts former president's NYC rink contracts on ice

value.excerpt: Six people, including two husband-and-wife pairs, were added to a federal conspiracy case Friday for alleged coordinate efforts in the Capitol attack.

value.title: GOP Rep. Lauren Boebert calls on Biden to lower flags in honor of Rush Limbaugh
value.excerpt: Rep. Lauren Boebert, R-Colo., called on President Biden on Friday night to order flags lowered to half-staff in honor the life of conservative radio legend Rush Limbaugh.

value.title: Biden remarks on China's Uighurs is 'bigotry masquerading as cultural sensitivity',' H.R. McMaster says
value.excerpt: Former national security adviser H.R. McMaster accused President Biden of "bigotry masquerading as cultural sensitivity," following a town hall event where the president addressed China’s human rights abuses.

value.title: Biden 'open' to lowering the $1.9 trillion coronavirus package price tag
value.excerpt: President Biden Friday defended the size of his $1.9 trillion coronavirus relief package even as he signaled to critics he'd be willing to make some trims to win their support.

value.excerpt: Iran has already shown it can pressure the Biden administration into granting concessions related to its nuclear weapons program, former Acting Director of National Intelligence Richard Grenell told "Your World" Friday.

value.title: 'America is back': Biden affirms transatlantic relationships
value.excerpt: Seeking a sharp break from the "America First" policies of his predecessor, President Joe Biden reaffirmed the US position of global leadership, the power of its alliances and the resilience of democracy in the United States and abroad.
